{{Infobox album | name = 0music | type = studio | artist = [[Melomics109]] | cover = Melomics109.jpg | alt = | released = {{start date|2014}} | recorded = [[Melomics109]] | venue = | studio = | genre = [[Symphonic music|Symphonic]], [[Minimalist music|Minimalist]], [[World music|World]], [[Electronic music|Electronic]] | length = {{Duration|m=42|s=35}} | label = | producer = | prev_title = | prev_year = | next_title = | next_year = }}
'''''0music''''' is the second album produced with [[Melomics]] technology. While the first one ([[Iamus (album)|Iamus' album]]) is a compilation of contemporary pieces fully composed by [[Iamus (computer)|Iamus]], ''0music'' compiles pieces of [[Popular music|popular genres]], composed and interpreted without any human intervention by [[Melomics109]],<ref>{{cite news | title= Artificial music: The computers that create melodies| |publisher= BBC Future| |last= Ball |first= Philip| publication-date =8 August 2014| url =http://www.bbc.com/future/story/20140808-music-like-never-heard-before/}}</ref> a [[computer cluster]] hosted at the [[University of Málaga|University of Malaga]]. The pieces in this album, and all the production of [[Melomics109]], is distributed under [[CC0#Zero .2F Public domain|CC0]] [[licensing]], and it is available in [[Audio file format|audible]] and editable ([[MIDI]]) formats.
The album was launched during a one-day [[symposium]] held in [[Málaga|Malaga]] on July 21, 2014.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://geb.uma.es/0music/ |title=0music: music after the advent of the computer-composer |access-date=2014-08-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160331060254/http://geb.uma.es/0music |archive-date=2016-03-31 |dead-url=yes |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Los límites de la música creada por ordenadores|url=http://www.abc.es/tecnologia/20140721/rc-limites-musica-creada-ordenadores-201407211959.html|accessdate=4 August 2014|newspaper=ABC|date=21 July 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Un ordenador que compone música, protagonista de simposio internacional|url=http://www.lavanguardia.com/local/sevilla/20140718/54411247040/un-ordenador-que-compone-musica-protagonista-de-simposio-internacional.html|accessdate=4 August 2014|newspaper=La Vanguardia|date=18 July 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal | title= Presentación de 0music| journal= ''University of Malaga press''| date =19 July 2014| url =http://www.uma.es/sala-de-prensa/noticias/presentacion-de-0music-segundo-disco-compuesto-y-grabajo-con-la-tecnologia-melonics/}}</ref>
