{{Infobox person | name = Leonard Logsdail |image=<!-- Deleted image removed: [[File:Leonard Logsdail.jpg|thumb|Leonard Logsdail in his Midtown Shop]] --> | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1950|9|11|df=yes}} | birth_place = London, England | occupation = Tailor | years_active = 1971–present }} '''Leonard Logsdail''' (born September 11, 1950 in [[London]], [[England]]) is a [[bespoke tailoring|bespoke]] [[tailor]], based in [[Manhattan]], [[New York (state)|New York]], specializing in men's [[suit (clothing)|suit]]s.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.cigaraficionado.com/webfeatures/show/id/Return-of-the-Smoking-Jacket_7364|title=Return of the Smoking Jacket {{!}} News & Features|last=Inc.|first=M. Shanken Communications,|work=CigarAficionado.com|access-date=2017-05-05|language=en}}</ref> He is described as one of the finest bespoke tailors in the men’s suit business.<ref name="Articles of Style">{{cite web |title= Lessons from a Master Cutter Feat. Leonard Logsdail |url= https://articlesofstyle.com/57369/lessons-from-a-master-cutter-feat-leonard-logsdail/|publisher=Articles of Style|first=Dan |last=Trepanier|date=February 2015}}</ref> All of Logsdail's suits are crafted and perfected on-site in his New York City location.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.permanentstyle.com/2010/03/a-glass-of-red-with-kempson-and-logsdail.html|title=A glass of red with Kempson and Logsdail|access-date=2017-05-05|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://nextluxury.com/mens-style-and-fashion/top-best-suit-brands-for-men/|title=Top 40 Best Suit Brands For Men - Where To Buy A Suit And What It Will Cost You|date=2017-02-24|work=Next Luxury|access-date=2017-05-05|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://timelessman.com.au/profiles/profile-leonard-logsdail-bespoke-tailor-new-york/|title=Leonard Logsdail -- Profile|access-date=2017-05-05|language=en-US}}</ref> He is credited for making [[Savile Row tailoring|Savile Row]] tailoring a local option in [[New York City|New York]].<ref name=":0">{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1999/10/17/style/the-return-of-the-suit-that-speaks-quietly-for-itself.html|title=The Return of the Suit That Speaks (Quietly) for Itself|last=Ferla|first=Ruth La|date=1999-10-17|work=The New York Times|access-date=2017-05-05|issn=0362-4331}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2005/07/30/business/im-here-to-see-a-man-about-a-suit.html|title=I'm Here to See a Man About a Suit|last=Hurt|first=Harry III|date=2005-07-30|work=The New York Times|access-date=2017-05-05|issn=0362-4331}}</ref> Logsdail is known for creating high-end suits, including lining jackets with [[Hermès|Hermes]] silk scarves.<ref name=":0" /><ref name=":2">{{Cite web|url=http://lenoeudpapillon.blogspot.com/2015/03/leonard-logsdail-famed-new-york-tailor.html|title=Le Noeud Papillon Of Sydney - For Lovers Of Bow Ties: Leonard Logsdail - Famed New York Tailor And Suit Maker For Some Of Your Favourite Cinema Characters - A Short Interview|date=2015-03-17|website=Le Noeud Papillon Of Sydney - For Lovers Of Bow Ties|access-date=2017-05-05}}</ref> [[CNBC]] talk show host, [[economist]] and [[fashion]] icon [[Lawrence Kudlow|Larry Kudlow]] has his suits made by Leonard Logsdail.<ref name=":0" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/roger-stone/best-dressed_b_1181148.html|title=StoneZone's 2011 Best and Worst Dressed|last=Stone|first=Roger|date=2012-01-03|website=Huffington Post|language=en-US|access-date=2017-05-08}}</ref> Logsdail has created suits for award-winning films, and is recognized as one of cinema's most sought-after tailors.<ref name="screen crush">{{cite web |title= Suiting Up for 'The Wolf of Wall Street': A Chat With One of Cinema's Most Sought-After Tailors|url=http://screencrush.com/the-wolf-of-wall-street-martin-scorsese-leonardo-dicaprio-leonard-logsdail|publisher=Screen Crush|first=Nick |last=Romano|date=December 2013}}</ref><ref name="Clothes on Film">{{cite web |title= Tailoring the Wolf of Wall Street|url= http://clothesonfilm.com/tailoring-the-wolf-of-wall-street/34636/ |publisher=Clothes on Film|first=Lord Christopher |last=Laverty |date=February 2014}}</ref> Logsdail has collaborated with esteemed film directors [[Steven Spielberg]], [[Robert De Niro|Robert de Niro]], [[Oliver Stone]], [[Ridley Scott]], and [[Martin Scorsese]].<ref name=":1">{{Cite web|url=http://www.vitalebarberiscanonico.com/tailors/245/leonard-logsdail|title=VBC {{!}} Tailors {{!}} Vitale Barberis Canonico|website=www.vitalebarberiscanonico.com|language=en|access-date=2017-05-05}}</ref><ref name="IMDb" /><ref name="screen crush" /><ref name=":2" /> He has had a [[Cameo appearance|cameo]] acting role as a tailor in [[The Wolf of Wall Street (2013 film)|The Wolf of Wall Street]], [[Wall Street: Money Never Sleeps|Wall Street 2: Money Never Sleeps]] and [[The Good Shepherd (film)|The Good Shepherd]].<ref name=":3">{{Cite web|url=https://www.ft.com/content/f737459c-f8e2-11df-99ed-00144feab49a|title=Bespoke suits in New York|website=Financial Times|access-date=2017-05-08}}</ref><ref name=":1" /><ref name="IMDb" /><ref name="screen crush" /><ref name=":2" />
==Career== Logsdail left traditional school at the age of 15, and spent 3 years in tailoring school before entering the industry with high aspirations and a passion for men’s suits.<ref name="interview">{{cite web |title= Interview With Leonard Logsdail|url=http://www.keikari.com/english/interview-with-leonard-logsdail/|publisher=Keikari|first=Ville|last=Raivio|date=May 2013}}</ref> By the age of 21, Logsdail started his own business. He opened his doors in 1971 on [[Carnaby Street]] in [[London]]. A few years later, he moved his business to [[Savile Row]].<ref name="Articles of Style" /> In 1991, Logsdail moved his business from [[Savile Row]] to midtown [[Manhattan]] [[New York (state)|New York]]. His [[atelier]] has remained in the same location since 1991, at [https://www.google.com/maps/place/9+E+53rd+St,+New+York,+NY+10022/@40.7601805,-73.9748051,20.06z/data=!4m5!3m4!1s0x89c258fba3670721:0x5f9cfecdbed66dad!8m2!3d40.7602806!4d-73.9749168 9 East 53rd Street, New York, NY].<ref name=":1" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.leonardlogsdail.com/contact/|title=Contact|website=Leonard Logsdail Bespoke Tailors|language=en-US|access-date=2017-05-05}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.thedailybeast.com/articles/2016/09/27/here-s-how-to-buy-a-tailored-suit|title=How Custom Tailoring Is Your Secret Weapon|last=Hayes|first=Eddie|date=2017-01-30|website=The Daily Beast|access-date=2017-05-05}}</ref>
==Personal life == While his tailoring business was in [[London]], Logsdail made business trips to the [[United States]], and on one of them, met a woman from [[Philadelphia]] who he fell in love with, and soon married in 1988.<ref name=":1" /> Logsdail and his wife Barbara reside in [[Stamford, Connecticut]]. He has 8 children. His son, Leonard, began working with him in 2012.<ref name=":2" />
