{{distinguish|text=the Seto dialect of the [[Fon language]]}} {{Infobox language |name = Seto |nativename = ''seto kiil´'' |states = [[Estonia]] |region = Southern [[Estonia]] |ethnicity = [[Setos]] |speakers = {{sigfig|12549|2}} |date = 2011 census |ref = <ref name="Statistikaamet">[[Statistics Estonia]] [http://pub.stat.ee/px-web.2001/Dialog/varval.asp?ma=RLE07&lang=2]</ref> |familycolor = Uralic |fam2 = [[Finnic languages|Finnic]] |fam3 = [[South Estonian]] |fam4 = [[Võro language|Võro]]? |isoexception= dialect |glotto=seto1241 |glottorefname= Seto }}
[[File:South Estonian today.PNG|thumb|South Estonian today. Seto is marked with light red colour.]] [[File:Seto valdo kaupa.jpg|thumb|Percentage of Seto speakers in Estonian municipalities according to the Estonian census 2011.]]
'''Seto''' (''seto kiil´'';<ref>[https://scholar.google.com/scholar?q=%22Seto+language%22&hl=en&lr=&btnG=Search Seto language @ google scholar]</ref> {{lang-et|setu keel}}) is a dialect of [[South Estonian]] spoken by 12,549 people.<ref name="Statistikaamet" /> It is sometimes identified as a dialect of [[Võro language|Võro]], or the two are described as one language, Seto-Võro. However, the ethnic identity of [[Setos]] (''Setokõsõq'') and [[Võros]] (''Võrokõsõq'') is quite distinct; Setos mostly inhabit the area near [[Estonia]]'s southeastern border with [[Russia]] in [[Setomaa]], and are primarily [[Eastern Orthodox Church|Eastern Orthodox]], while Võros are traditionally [[Lutheranism|Lutherans]] and live in [[Võru County]].
== Language sample == Article 1 of the [[Universal Declaration of Human Rights]]:
* Seto: ''Kõik inemiseq sünnüseq avvo ja õiguisi poolõst ütesugumaidsist. Näile om annõt mudsu ja süämetun'stus ja nä piät ütstõõsõga vele muudu läbi kjauma.'' * [[Võro language|Võro]]: ''Kõik inemiseq sünnüseq avvo ja õiguisi poolõst ütesugumaidsis. Näile om annõt mudsu ja süämetunnistus ja nä piät ütstõõsõga vele muudu läbi käümä.'' * [[Estonian language|Estonian]]: ''Kõik inimesed sünnivad vabadena ja võrdsetena oma väärikuselt ja õigustelt. Neile on antud mõistus ja südametunnistus ja nende suhtumist üksteisesse peab kandma vendluse vaim.'' * [[Finnish language|Finnish]]: ''Kaikki ihmiset syntyvät vapaina ja tasavertaisina arvoltaan ja oikeuksiltaan. Heille on annettu järki ja omatunto, ja heidän on toimittava toisiaan kohtaan veljeyden hengessä.'' * [[English language|English]]: ''All human beings are born free and equal in dignity and rights. They are endowed with reason and conscience and should act towards one another in a spirit of brotherhood. ''
